            <p>
            
              According to the Bureau of Labor Statistics consumer price index, the dollar experienced an average inflation rate of <span class="highlight">2.07% per year</span>.
            
            
              Prices in 2018 are
              
                <span class="highlight">44.6% higher</span> than
              
              prices in 2000.
            
            </p><p>
            In other words, $100 in the year 2000 is equivalent in purchasing power to $144.59 in 2018, a difference of $44.59 over 18 years.
            </p>

            
            
              <p>
