            <p style="font-size:20px; line-height: 1.3">
              
                <h3>How to calculate the inflation rate for $100 since 2000</h3>
              
              Start with the inflation rate formula:
              <br><br>
              <span class="fraction">CPI in 2018 / CPI in 2000</span> <span class="middle">* 2000 USD value = 2018 USD value</span>
              <br><br>
              Then plug in <a href="http://www.in2013dollars.com/articles/consumer-price-index-since-1913/" target="_blank">historical CPI values</a>.  The U.S. CPI was 172.2 in the year 2000 and 248.991 in 2018:
              <br><br>
              <span class="fraction">248.991 / 172.2</span> <span class="middle">* $100 = <strong>$144.59</strong></span>
              <br><br>
              $100 in 2000 has the same "purchasing power" as $144.59 in 2018.
            </p>
